{
  "texts": [
    "Probability randomizationAdversarial privacy attacks, specifically membership inference attacks, target machine learning classifiers and infer input datasets by interpreting the confidence score and probability of the queried output.",
    "Adding noise to the output or intentionally interrupting the confidence probability score leads to the privacy preservation of machine learning, preventing adversaries from inferring confidential details of the victim model.",
    "Membership inference guard (MemGuard) [74] is one of the solutions designed to preserve the privacy of machine learning models against membership inference attacks by adding randomized noise to each of the score vectors with a specified probability of accuracy loss and makes machine learning-based binary classifier resilient to mitigate membership inference attack.",
    "However, the solution is only tested for securing neural networks under the black box attack settings.",
    "Pre-trainingZ."
  ]
}